{"title_page": "Smokepurpp", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Smokepurpp\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Smokepurpp.jpg\n| caption          = Smokepurpp in May 2018\n| birth_name       = Omar Jeffery Pineiro\n| alias            = {{flatlist|\n* Lil Purpp  \n* Lil Water<ref>{{cite web |title=LMFAAO freestyle 12.18.2010 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4VyPQRszo0Y |website=YouTube |accessdate=7 January 2019 |date=December 18, 2010\n|author=yungWestTV}}</ref>\n}}\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1997|5|15}}\n| birth_place      = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S.\n| origin           = [[Miami]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Emo rap]]\n* [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/smokepurpp-deadstar/|title=Smokepurpp \"Deadstar\" Album Review|author=David Drake|date=October 11, 2017|accessdate=2017-10-16}}</ref>\n* [[punk rap]]<ref>https://www.vulture.com/2017/12/the-year-rap-overtook-pop.html</ref>\n* [[SoundCloud rap]]<ref name=nytimeslilsmoketrip>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/21/arts/music/xxxtentacion-question-6ix9ine-day69-review.html|access-date=2018-06-16|language=en-US|title=Two SoundCloud Rap Outlaws Push Boundaries From the Fringes|author=Jon Caramanica|date=2018-03-21|quote=And yet something slightly different has been happening: Many of the sound\u2019s key players \u2014 Lil Pump, Smokepurpp, Trippie Redd \u2014 have been absorbed into the music industry, becoming a kind of farm team for hip-hop\u2019s mainstream.}}</ref>\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Rapper\n* singer\n* songwriter\n* record producer\n}}\n| years_active     = 2010\u2013present<ref>{{cite web |title=LMFAAO freestyle 12.18.2010 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4VyPQRszo0Y |website=YouTube |accessdate=7 January 2019 |date=December 18, 2010}}</ref>\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Todd Moscowitz|Alamo]]\n* [[Interscope Records|Interscope]] <small>(current)</small>\n* [[Cactus Jack Records|Cactus Jack]] <small>(former)</small>\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Lil Pump]]\n* [[Trippie Redd]]\n* [[Travis Scott]]\n* [[Murda Beatz]]\n* [[Ronny J]]\n* [[Lil Peep]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Omar Jeffery Pineiro'''<ref>http://repertoire.bmi.com/Catalog.aspx?detail=writerid&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&keyid=550484157&subid=0</ref> (born May 15, 1997), known professionally as '''Smokepurpp''', is an American rapper, singer, songwriter and record producer. Originally a record producer, Pineiro later found success on the audio distribution platform [[SoundCloud]] in 2016 after his song \"Audi\" became popular. Pineiro was part of the \"[[SoundCloud rap]]\" movement, due to his influence on artists such as [[Lil Pump]] who have since entered the mainstream music market.  \n \nPineiro released his debut commercial mixtape ''[[Deadstar (mixtape)|Deadstar]]'' on September 28, 2017,<ref name=\"XXL201709\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2017/09/smokepurpp-deadstar-mixtape/|title=Smokepurpp's 'Deadstar' Is Finally Here|website=XXL Mag|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> and the mixtape peaked at number 42 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] albums chart.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/billboard-200/song/1047588|title=Smokepurpp Deadstar Chart History|work=Billboard|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nOmar Jeffery Pineiro was born on May 15, 1997<ref name=Carter>{{cite web|last1=Carter|first1=Brooke|title=SmokePurpp Net Worth 2017 \u2013 How Much Is He Worth Now?|url=http://gazettereview.com/2017/06/smokepurpp-net-worth-much-worth-now/|website=Gazette Review|accessdate=24 November 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170602100101/http://gazettereview.com/2017/06/smokepurpp-net-worth-much-worth-now/|archivedate=2 June 2017}}</ref> in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]].<ref name=RS/> He and his family moved to  [[Miami]], [[Florida]] when he was three years old.<ref name=RS>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/look-at-me-the-noisy-soundcloud-revolution-changing-rap-w485101|title=Look At Me!: The Noisy, Blown-Out SoundCloud Revolution Redefining Rap|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> Speaking on his upbringing, Pineiro described himself during high school as a calm individual who surrounded himself with diverse groups of people.<ref>{{Citation|last=No Jumper|title=The SmokePurpp Interview - No Jumper|date=2016-10-06|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rQNQezzYq3U|accessdate=2017-10-11}}</ref>\n\nPineiro began his music career as a producer, a hobby he picked up due to boredom. While doing this, he had a major influence in getting his friend [[Lil Pump]] into rapping as well. He began to rap when no one bought his produced instrumentals and due to the success of several tracks on the audio distribution platform SoundCloud, Pineiro dropped out of high school in his senior year.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/smokepurpp-mn0003622501/biography|title=Smokepurpp {{!}} Biography & History {{!}} AllMusic|website=AllMusic|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>\n\nHis musical influences are [[Kanye West]], [[Young Thug]] and Lucky.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8508958/smokepurpp-video-interview</ref>\n\n==Career==\nPineiro originally started to pursue music in high school, starting as a producer. Pineiro began to rap due to the lack of people actually buying his produced instrumentals.<ref>{{Citation|last=Mass Appeal|title=Open Space: SmokePurpp|date=2017-05-10|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vy_qRCQr1ag|accessdate=2017-10-11}}</ref> Pineiro's first song was released on [[SoundCloud]] in 2015, but Pineiro quickly deleted it due to its lack of quality, soon uploading his second song, \"Live Off A Lick\" featuring Florida native rapper [[XXXTentacion]].<ref>{{Citation|title=smokepurpp ft. xxxtentacion - Live Off A Lick [prod. YUNG TREL]|url=https://soundcloud.com/smokepurpp/smokepurpp-ft-xxxtentacion-live-off-a-lick-prod-yung-trel|language=en|accessdate=2017-10-11}}</ref> Pineiro eventually dropped out of high school due to his budding music career.<ref name=\":1\" /> Pineiro later released his first music video on September 23, 2014, titled \"It\u2019s Nothin\" with rapper Lil Ominous, whom is also Pineiro's cousin.\n\nIn March 2017, Pineiro signed joint venture record deal with [[Todd Moscowitz|Alamo Records]] and [[Interscope Records]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/03/smokepurpp-signs-record-deal/|title=Smokepurpp Signs to Todd Moscowitz\u2019s Alamo Records - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> Following this, he announced his debut mixtape on March 9, 2017 on the social media platform Twitter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/smokepurpp/status/839684278921347074?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&ref_url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/03/smokepurpp-signs-record-deal/|title=New tape on the way... pic.twitter.com/1gLi1sEY5h|last=purpp|first=lil|date=<!--7:48 PM - -->8 March 2017|website=@smokepurpp|language=en|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> Several days later on March 14, 2017, Pineiro announced that his debut commercial mixtape would be titled ''Deadstar''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2017/03/smokepurpp-deadtstar-mixtape-woah/|title=Smokepurpp Announces 'Deadtstar' Mixtape, Drops 'Woah' - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>\n\nPineiro released his commercial debut single, \"Audi\" in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2017/05/smokepurpp-goes-nuts-on-new-song-audi/|title=Smokepurpp Goes Nuts on New Song 'Audi'|website=XXL Mag|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> The single soon became his biggest song with over 25 million plays on SoundCloud<ref>{{Citation|title=Audi.|url=https://soundcloud.com/smokepurpp/audi|language=en|accessdate=2017-10-11}}</ref> and 122 million streams on Spotify<ref>{{Citation|title=Audi.|date=2017-05-19|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/3l1nALhJZP4WiIwLEluCC6|language=en|accessdate=2017-10-11}}</ref> as of October 2017. In September 2017, Pineiro announced that the release date for ''Deadstar'' was September 22, releasing the single \"Bless Yo Trap\" following the announcement.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7957085/smokepurpp-deadstar-release-date-bless-yo-trap|title=Smokepurpp Announces 'DEADSTAR' Release Date, Premieres New Song 'Bless Yo Trap'|work=Billboard|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> Pineiro announced later on that ''Deadstar'' would be delayed, stating no expected release date.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/smokepurpp-reveals-deadstar-delay-tm88-production-new-video.42683.html|title=Smokepurpp Reveals \"DEADSTAR\" Delay, TM88 Production|work=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>\n\nOn September 28, 2017, Pineiro released ''Deadstar''. The mixtape included features from artists such as [[Chief Keef]], [[Juicy J]] and [[Travis Scott]].<ref name=\"XXL201709\" /> The mixtape debuted at 42 on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart.<ref name=\":0\" /> Following the release of the mixtape, On November 8, 2017, Pineiro was on the MTV show ''[[Total Request Live|TRL]]'', where he announced that he has a collaboration mixtape coming soon with [[Murda Beatz]] titled ''[[Bless Yo Trap]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://trl.mtv.com/news/3046226/smokepurpp-tamar-braxton-trl-appearance/|title=SMOKEPURPP & TAMAR BRAXTON LIVED UP TO THE HYPE ON TRL - MTV|website=MTV|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-02}}</ref> He later released 2 singles from the mixtape called ''123'' and ''Do Not Disturb'', the latter which featured [[Lil Yachty]] and [[Offset (rapper)|Offset]] from the [[Migos]]. The mixtape was released on April 13, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/04/stream-smokepurpp-murda-beatz-bless-yo-trap-project|title=Listen to Smokepurpp and Murda Beatz's Joint Project 'Bless Yo Trap'|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref>\n\nOn March 20, 2018, while Pineiro was at [[SXSW]], he did an interview with [[Nardwuar the Human Serviette]], and in that interview, Nardwuar exposed that he has a project coming in 2018 called ''Sound of Space'', along with his ''Deadstar 2'' project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q|title=Nardwuar vs. Smokepurpp|date=Mar 20, 2018|website=YouTube}}</ref>\n\nOn April 19, 2019, Pineiro released his EP ''Lost Planet'' via Alamo Records. The EP includes [[guest appearances]] from fellow rappers Gunna, Lil Pump, and [[NLE Choppa]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/albums/Smokepurpp/Lost-planet|title=Lost Planet by Smokepurpp|website=Genius|language=en|access-date=April 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Studio albums and selected details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/billboard-200|title=Smokepurpp Chart History: Billboard 200|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/canadian-albums|title=Smokepurpp Chart History: Canadian Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Deadstar 2]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ventsmagazine.com/2019/10/31/smokepurpp-announces-debut-album-deadstar-2-executive-produced-by-mike-dean/|title=Smokepurpp Announces Debut Album Deadstar 2, Executive Produced by Mike Dean|last=Frometa|first=RJ|date=October 31, 2019|accessdate=November 8, 2019|work=Vents Magazine}}</ref>\n|\n*Released: December 13, 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/deadstar-2/1490675173|title=Deadstar 2 by Smokepurpp|website=Apple Music|accessdate=December 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*Label: [[Todd Moscowitz|Alamo]], [[Interscope Records|Interscope]] \n*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| 137 || 86\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays and selected details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Extended play details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Up Now Fuck Next''\n|\n* Released: May 12, 2017\n*Label: Alamo, Interscope\n*Format: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Lost Planet''\n|\n* Released: April 19, 2019\n*Label: Alamo, Interscope\n*Format: Digital download\n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with selected details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"BB200\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US R&B/HH]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-albums|title=Smokepurpp Chart History: R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top Rap Albums|US Rap]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/rap-albums|title=Smokepurpp Chart History: Rap Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/canadian-albums|title=Smokepurpp Chart History: Canadian Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 11, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Deadstar (mixtape)|Deadstar]]''\n|\n* Released: September 29, 2017\n* Label: Alamo, Interscope\n* Formats: Digital download\n| 42 || 24 || 16 || 77\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Bless Yo Trap]]''<br />{{small|(with [[Murda Beatz]])}}\n|\n* Released: April 13, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/smokepurpp-confirms-bless-yo-trap-drop-with-magical-artwork-news.47724.html|title=Smokepurpp Confirms \"Bless Yo Trap\" Drop With Magical Artwork|work=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=April 12, 2018}}</ref>\n* Label: Alamo, Interscope\n* Formats: Digital download\n| 40 || 22 || 17 || 30\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n\n==== As lead artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Bubbling Under Hot 100|US<br>Bub.]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/bubbling-under-hot-100|title=Smokepurpp Chart History: Bubbling Under Hot 100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 27, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/smokepurpp/chart-history/CAN|title=Smokepurpp Chart History {{!}} Billboard|last=|first=|dat